node.title: Claire quit her job and sold her possessions — then Omicron changed everything
node.description: Claire Ebersohn was only two days away from starting her new life in Australia but global panic over the Omicron strain of COVID-19 has locked her out of the country.

node.title: Obeid-backed development at Hawks Nest to face legal challenge from traditional owners
node.description: Plans for a controversial apartment development in the beachside town of Hawks Nest, secretly backed by the family of corrupt NSW politician Eddie Obeid, are set to be challenged in court by traditional owners.

node.title: Large attendance variations in Auckland schools
node.description: Auckland schools are reporting wildly different attendance rates with some families refusing to send children back to class.

node.title: CIA publishes new account describing "challenges" of briefing Trump
node.description: "Trump was like Nixon, suspicious and insecure about the intelligence process, but unlike Nixon in the way he reacted," according to a new  account.

node.title: WTA Suspends Tournaments in China Over Missing Tennis Star Peng Shuai
node.description: Steve Simon said Wednesday that the women’s tennis tour would not stage tournaments in China, including Hong Kong, because he has been unable to communicate with Peng despite repeated attempts.

node.title: Women's Tennis Tournaments in China, Hong Kong Suspended Amid Peng Shuai Controversy
node.description: "China's leaders have left the WTA with no choice," WTA Chairman Scott Simon said on Wednesday regarding the decision to suspend tournaments.

node.title: Internet Roasts Woman After Her Hilarious Pumpkin Pie Fail Goes Viral
node.description: "Did you try to bake the pie and self-clean the oven at the same time?" asked one Facebook commenter.

node.title: Oxford School Shooter Identified as 15-Year-Old Ethan Crumbley, Faces Adult Charges
node.description: The teenage suspect in Tuesday's shooting was named by the prosecutor hours after a fourth student died.

node.title: Champagne more expensive but local sparkling makers say their bubbles are just as good
node.description: Australia is in the midst of a champagne shortage and there is no chance of summer discounts or bulk deals this year, according to local importers.

node.title: Older and wiser Warrior returns to NRL home
node.description: Sitting up there wearing the old colours and once again part of a club that never should have forced him out in the first place, he sure looked like the old Shaun Johnson.

node.title: 'I Didn't Steal It': TikToker Claims Issues With Security System in Viral Video
node.description: While at a self-checkout station, the TikToker said he scanned his item but the system did not recognize it and an employee had to respond.

node.title: ‘Annie Live!’: Coming Soon to Your Living Room
node.description: NBC’s latest TV musical airs Thursday night and features three women of color — Taraji P. Henson, Nicole Scherzinger and Celina Smith — in leading roles.

node.title: Alvin Lucier, Probing Composer of Soundscapes, Is Dead at 91
node.description: His experimental music was rooted in the physics of sound and might yield unpredictable results — in one instance a Beatles song emanating from a teapot.

node.title: Which Films Lead the Biggest Best-Picture Race in Years?
node.description: With epics like “West Side Story” and biopics like “King Richard” in contention, Oscar voters have plenty of choices in a category that’s now set at 10 slots.

node.title: Oil Producers Face Omicron Uncertainty and Rebellious Customers
node.description: OPEC and Russia want to bolster oil prices after a 10 percent drop last week. But they also need to consider the release of oil reserves by the U.S. and other countries.

node.title: Recovering Travel Industry Tries to Forge Ahead as Questions Surround Omicron Variant
node.description: The travel impacts come as many questions still remain about the highly-mutated variant and how it may be compared to other strains.

node.title: Alec Baldwin Claims He Didn't Pull Trigger On Gun That Killed Halyna Hutchins On 'Rust' Set
node.description: "There are no words to convey my shock and sadness regarding the tragic accident that took the life of Halyna Hutchins," Baldwin said after the incident.

node.title: 58.4M Tons of Plastic Will Pollute World's Oceans Every Year By 2030: Report
node.description: The report showed that a DNA study found bacteria and viruses from humans and animals on plastic that could potentially spread disease.

node.title: Capitol Rioter Loses Bid to Delay Sentence to Fulfill 'Holiday Obligations' to Children
node.description: Rasha Abual-Ragheb, who pleaded guilty in the Capitol riot, has sole custody of her two school-aged children.

node.title: SCOTUS Hearing Suggests Conservative Majority Ready to Overturn Roe, Uphold Mississippi Ban
node.description: With Justices Kavanaugh and Barrett seemingly uninterested in the narrow decision eyed by Chief Justice Roberts, the court appears likely to overturn Roe.

node.title: Scientists identify armoured dinosaur with tail like Aztec weapon
node.description: The Stegouros elengassen is a four-legged creature which lived in what is now South America's southernmost tip during the Cretaceous Period.

node.title: We can't stop workplace sexual harassment without banning non-disclosure agreements
node.description: NDAs are increasingly used against employees who make complaints about discrimination and harassment. But the practice has a chilling effect on people's willingness to speak out, and must be eradicated, write Maria O'Sullivan and Judith Bessant.

node.title: High Court rules against police in unprecedented proceeds-of-crime case
node.description: The High Court has ruled against the police who are trying to avoid paying up if they lose an unprecedented proceeds-of-crime case over a fatal explosion that killed a young welder.

node.title: CDC confirms first case of Omicron variant in U.S.
node.description: An individual in California who had recently traveled to South Africa tested positive for the strain, the health agency said.

node.title: The Crash of Two Airplanes and the Crisis at Boeing
node.description: Peter Robison’s “Flying Blind” tells the full story of two air disasters and Boeing’s role in the crashes.

node.title: Alec Baldwin Says He ‘Didn’t Pull the Trigger’ in ‘Rust’ Killing
node.description: The actor said in a brief excerpt from an upcoming interview with ABC News that he had not pulled the trigger when the gun he was holding went off, killing the cinematographer.

node.title: 6 Hurt as Midnight Explosion Rocks Brooklyn Block
node.description: Dozens were displaced by the blast. Its cause was not yet clear, but a neighbor said he reported smelling gas the day before.

node.title: The C.D.C. tells airlines to identify passengers who had recently been in southern Africa.
node.description: The agency said it was “issuing this directive to prevent the importation and spread of a communicable disease of public health importance,” an apparent reference to the new Omicron variant.

node.title: Senate Republicans Threaten Shutdown Over Vaccine Mandates
node.description: With federal funding set to lapse on Friday, President Biden’s vaccine-and-testing mandate for large employers has emerged as a sticking points over a stopgap spending bill.

node.title: Biden Jokes Only Santa Can Keep Promise of Gifts Arriving on Time Amid Supply Chain Woes
node.description: The president said the CEOs of major retailers recently told him "their inventories are up" and their "shelves are well-stocked" heading into the holidays.
